Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi has discussed the outcomes and achievements of his trip to South Pacific Island nations. He said China practices the diplomatic principle of equality among all countries with practical actions, and has deeply felt the strong expectation of Pacific Island countries for developing cooperation with China. He said during his trip, China and Pacific Island nations have signed and reached a great deal of bilateral cooperation outcomes, covering 15 areas, including Belt and Road cooperation, climate change, and COVID-19 pandemic response.